{"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"display_name":"Python 3","language":"python","name":"python3"},"language_info":{"name":"python","version":"3.12.12","mimetype":"text/x-python","codemirror_mode":{"name":"ipython","version":3},"pygments_lexer":"ipython3","nbconvert_exporter":"python","file_extension":".py"},"kaggle":{"accelerator":"none","dataSources":[{"sourceType":"datasetVersion","sourceId":14951015,"datasetId":9568928,"databundleVersionId":15821229},{"sourceType":"datasetVersion","sourceId":15033352,"datasetId":9623528,"databundleVersionId":15911891}],"dockerImageVersionId":31286,"isInternetEnabled":true,"language":"python","sourceType":"notebook","isGpuEnabled":false}},"nbformat_minor":5,"nbformat":4,"cells":[{"source":"<a href=\"https://www.kaggle.com/code/djouaheryasmine/max-sat-branch-and-bound?scriptVersionId=301680092\" target=\"_blank\"><img align=\"left\" alt=\"Kaggle\" title=\"Open in Kaggle\" src=\"https://kaggle.com/static/images/open-in-kaggle.svg\"></a>","metadata":{},"cell_type":"markdown"},{"id":"01fe7c78-a2f4-4704-b5b8-ddc32b7f2068","cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Branch and Bound pour MAX-SAT\n**Basé sur :** Zhang, Shen & Manyà — *Exact Algorithms for MAX-SAT* (2003)\n\n---\n\n## 1. Le problème MAX-SAT\n\n**MAX-SAT** est une généralisation du problème de satisfaisabilité booléenne (SAT). L'entrée est une formule booléenne en **forme normale conjonctive (CNF)** — un ensemble de clauses, chaque clause étant une disjonction de littéraux.\n\n**Objectif :** Trouver une assignation de vérité qui **maximise le nombre de clauses satisfaites** (ou équivalemment, minimise le nombre de clauses fausses).\n\n**Exemple :**\n$$F = (x_1 \\lor x_2) \\land (\\neg x_1 \\lor x_3) \\land (\\neg x_2 \\lor \\neg x_3)$$\n\nMAX-SAT est MAX-SNP-complete. Aucune approximation polynomiale n'existe sauf si P = NP.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Approche Branch and Bound\n\nL'algorithme de Zhang et al. fonctionne comme une procédure **DPLL** adaptée à MAX-SAT :\n\n**Principe général :**\n- On explore l'arbre de recherche des assignations (arbre binaire de profondeur $n$)\n- À chaque nœud, on choisit une variable non assignée et on branche sur `True` / `False`\n- On maintient un compteur global `min_false` = meilleur nombre de clauses fausses trouvé jusqu'ici\n- **Élagage (bound) :** si le coût courant `k` (clauses déjà fausses) dépasse `min_false`, on abandonne la branche\n\n**Mécanisme des clauses unitaires (`u(x)`) :**\nQuand on assigne un littéral, certaines clauses deviennent unitaires (un seul littéral restant). Ces clauses sont retirées et comptabilisées dans `u(x)` — le nombre de clauses unitaires qui **seront fausses** si on assigne ce littéral dans le mauvais sens.\n\n**Complexité :** $O(b \\cdot 2^n)$ où $b$ est le nombre maximum d'occurrences d'une variable et $n$ le nombre de variables.\n\n---\n\n### Initialisation\n\n| Variable | Rôle | Valeur initiale |\n|---|---|---|\n| `min_false` | Le meilleur score trouvé dans toute la recherche | $\\infty$ — rien exploré encore |\n| `k` | Les clauses fausses déjà accumulées sur le chemin courant | $0$ — rien assigné encore |\n| `u(x)` | Les clauses fausses anticipées si on assigne $x$ à faux | $0$ — formule intacte |\n| `A` | Les décisions prises jusqu'au nœud courant | $\\emptyset$ — rien décidé encore |\n\n---\n\n### Choix du nœud (branchement)\n\nOn choisit une variable non assignée dans la formule courante. Le papier suggère de trier les variables par **nombre d'occurrences décroissant** — les variables les plus fréquentes en premier. On crée deux branches : $x = \\text{True}$ et $x = \\text{False}$.\n\n---\n\n### Type de parcours\n\n**Profondeur d'abord (DFS).** On descend complètement dans une branche avant d'en explorer une autre. C'est ce qui permet de trouver rapidement une première solution et de faire descendre `min_false` tôt pour élaguer efficacement.\n\n---\n\n### Fonction objectif\n\n$$\\text{Minimiser } k = \\text{nombre de clauses fausses sous l'assignation } A$$\n\n---\n\n### Fonction d'évaluation (bound)\n\n$$f(\\text{nœud}) = k + u(x)$$\n\n- `k` = clauses déjà fausses depuis la racine\n- `u(x)` = clauses unitaires qui deviendront fausses si on prend ce chemin\n\nElle donne une **borne inférieure** du coût réel — le vrai coût final ne peut qu'être supérieur ou égal.\n\n---\n\n### Critère d'élagage\n\n$$k + u(x) \\geq \\text{min\\_false} \\Rightarrow \\text{on coupe la branche}$$\n\nSi la borne inférieure dépasse déjà le meilleur score connu, continuer est inutile.\n\n---\n\n### Critères d'arrêt\n\n| Situation | Action |\n|---|---|\n| $k + u(x) \\geq \\text{min\\_false}$ | Arrêt de la branche, on remonte |\n| $\\|A\\| = n$ (feuille atteinte) | Arrêt de la branche, on compare $k$ avec `min_false` |\n| Tout l'arbre exploré ou élagué | Arrêt global, `min_false` est la réponse optimale |\n\n---\n\n### Mise à jour de la solution\n\nQuand on atteint une feuille ($|A| = n$) :\n\n```\nsi k < min_false:\n    min_false = k\n    meilleure_assignation = A\n```\n---\n\n## 3. L'algorithme (structure)\n\n```\nBRANCH_BOUND_MAX_SAT(S):\n    Initialiser u(x) = 0 pour tout littéral x\n    min_false = ∞\n    BB_MAX_SAT(S, k=0, A=∅)\n    retourner min_false\n\nBB_MAX_SAT(S, k, A):\n    si |A| = n:                          # assignation complète\n        si k < min_false:\n            min_false = k\n        retourner\n\n    Choisir un littéral x non assigné dans S\n\n    # Branche x = False  (assigner ¬x à True)\n    si non_pur(x) ET u(x) + k < min_false:\n        S' = appliquer(S, ¬x)  et enregistrer clauses unitaires\n        BB_MAX_SAT(S', k + u(x), A ∪ {¬x})\n        annuler()\n\n    # Branche x = True\n    si u(¬x) + k < min_false:\n        S' = appliquer(S, x)   et enregistrer clauses unitaires\n        BB_MAX_SAT(S', k + u(¬x), A ∪ {x})\n        annuler()\n```\n","metadata":{}},{"id":"3bcc4c81-7c13-4e94-bb49-77daf2e313d6","cell_type":"markdown","source":"---\n## 4. Implémentation Python","metadata":{}},{"id":"32ac37e4-fe0e-4213-8602-c6773beb100c","cell_type":"code","source":"import time\nimport random\nfrom typing import List, Tuple, Optional\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n# Représentation :\n#   - Une clause est un frozenset d'entiers\n#   - Un littéral positif x  → entier  x  (x > 0)\n#   - Un littéral négatif ¬x → entier -x  (x > 0)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n\nclass MaxSATSolver:\n    def __init__(self, clauses, n_vars):\n        self.n = n_vars\n        self.initial_clauses = [frozenset(c) for c in clauses]\n        self.min_false = float('inf')\n        self.best_assignment = None\n        self.nodes_visited = 0\n\n    def _apply_literal(self, clauses, literal):\n        new_clauses = []\n        false_count = 0\n        for clause in clauses:\n            if literal in clause:\n                continue\n            elif -literal in clause:\n                reduced = clause - {-literal}\n                if len(reduced) == 0:\n                    false_count += 1\n                else:\n                    new_clauses.append(reduced)\n            else:\n                new_clauses.append(clause)\n        return new_clauses, false_count\n\n    def _get_unassigned_var(self, clauses, assigned_vars):\n        counts = {}\n        for clause in clauses:\n            for lit in clause:\n                v = abs(lit)\n                if v not in assigned_vars:\n                    counts[v] = counts.get(v, 0) + 1\n        if not counts:\n            for v in range(1, self.n + 1):\n                if v not in assigned_vars:\n                    return v\n            return None\n        return max(counts, key=counts.get)\n\n    def _bb(self, clauses, k, assignment, assigned_vars):\n        self.nodes_visited += 1\n\n        if len(assigned_vars) == self.n:\n            total_false = k + len(clauses)\n            if total_false < self.min_false:\n                self.min_false = total_false\n                self.best_assignment = dict(assignment)\n            return\n\n        if k >= self.min_false:\n            return\n\n        var = self._get_unassigned_var(clauses, assigned_vars)\n        if var is None:\n            total_false = k + len(clauses)\n            if total_false < self.min_false:\n                self.min_false = total_false\n                self.best_assignment = dict(assignment)\n            return\n\n        assigned_vars = assigned_vars | {var}\n\n        # Branche True\n        if k < self.min_false:\n            new_clauses, added_false = self._apply_literal(clauses, var)\n            assignment[var] = True\n            self._bb(new_clauses, k + added_false, assignment, assigned_vars)\n\n        # Branche False\n        if k < self.min_false:\n            new_clauses, added_false = self._apply_literal(clauses, -var)\n            assignment[var] = False\n            self._bb(new_clauses, k + added_false, assignment, assigned_vars)\n\n        if var in assignment:\n            del assignment[var]\n\n    def solve(self):\n        self.min_false = float('inf')\n        self.best_assignment = None\n        self.nodes_visited = 0\n        self._bb(self.initial_clauses, 0, {}, set())\n        return self.min_false, self.best_assignment\n\n\ndef count_satisfied(clauses, assignment):\n    satisfied = 0\n    for clause in clauses:\n        for lit in clause:\n            var, pos = abs(lit), lit > 0\n            if assignment.get(var, False) == pos:\n                satisfied += 1\n                break\n    return satisfied","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-04T10:48:51.006089Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-04T10:48:51.006592Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-04T10:48:51.029731Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-04T10:48:51.006549Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-04T10:48:51.028462Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":1},{"id":"8255afd0-7d93-4b58-8459-50bdb1548cdf","cell_type":"markdown","source":"### Test rapide sur un exemple simple","metadata":{}},{"id":"fa39d732-63c7-4d3b-8c22-253de4412410","cell_type":"code","source":"# Exemple : 3 variables, 4 clauses\n# (x1 ∨ x2) ∧ (¬x1 ∨ x3) ∧ (¬x2 ∨ ¬x3) ∧ (¬x1 ∨ ¬x2)\nclauses_ex = [\n    [1, 2],\n    [-1, 3],\n    [-2, -3],\n    [-1, -2]\n]\n\nsolver = MaxSATSolver(clauses_ex, n_vars=3)\nmin_false, best_assign = solver.solve()\n\nprint(f\"Clauses fausses minimum : {min_false}\")\nprint(f\"Clauses satisfaites     : {len(clauses_ex) - min_false} / {len(clauses_ex)}\")\nprint(f\"Meilleure assignation   : {best_assign}\")\nprint(f\"Nœuds visités           : {solver.nodes_visited}\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-04T10:49:48.440915Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-04T10:49:48.44128Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-04T10:49:48.449318Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-04T10:49:48.441251Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-04T10:49:48.447887Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Clauses fausses minimum : 0\nClauses satisfaites     : 4 / 4\nMeilleure assignation   : {1: True, 3: True, 2: False}\nNœuds visités           : 5\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":3},{"id":"7bc5f27b-8d7d-42f2-9a1c-b8e34e6fab92","cell_type":"code","source":"# Formule insatisfaisable : contradiction pure\n# (x1) ∧ (¬x1) ∧ (x2) ∧ (¬x2)\nclauses_unsat = [\n    [1],\n    [-1],\n    [2],\n    [-2]\n]\n\nsolver = MaxSATSolver(clauses_unsat, n_vars=2)\nmin_false, best_assign = solver.solve()\n\nprint(f\"Clauses fausses minimum : {min_false}\")\nprint(f\"Clauses satisfaites     : {len(clauses_unsat) - min_false} / {len(clauses_unsat)}\")\nprint(f\"Meilleure assignation   : {best_assign}\")\n\n# Vérification manuelle\nfor x1 in [True, False]:\n    for x2 in [True, False]:\n        assign = {1: x1, 2: x2}\n        sat = count_satisfied(clauses_unsat, assign)\n        print(f\"x1={x1}, x2={x2} → satisfaites={sat}/4\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-04T10:49:53.06731Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-04T10:49:53.067639Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-04T10:49:53.075769Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-04T10:49:53.06761Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-04T10:49:53.074796Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Clauses fausses minimum : 2\nClauses satisfaites     : 2 / 4\nMeilleure assignation   : {1: True, 2: True}\nx1=True, x2=True → satisfaites=2/4\nx1=True, x2=False → satisfaites=2/4\nx1=False, x2=True → satisfaites=2/4\nx1=False, x2=False → satisfaites=2/4\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":4},{"id":"7d36e39d-a5e9-435b-a144-ce7fe46b55e1","cell_type":"markdown","source":"---\n## 5. Évaluation de l'efficacité\n\nOn évalue l'algorithme selon deux axes :\n1. **Effet du ratio clauses/variables** (`c = m/n`) sur le temps et les nœuds explorés\n2. **Scalabilité** en fonction du nombre de variables `n`","metadata":{}},{"id":"2297c098-3430-432e-af55-15841120da73","cell_type":"code","source":"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\nimport numpy as np\n\n# ── Générateur d'instances aléatoires k-SAT ──\ndef random_ksat(n_vars, n_clauses, k=3, seed=None):\n    \"\"\"Génère une instance MAX-k-SAT aléatoire.\"\"\"\n    rng = random.Random(seed)\n    clauses = []\n    for _ in range(n_clauses):\n        vars_chosen = rng.sample(range(1, n_vars + 1), k)\n        clause = [v if rng.random() > 0.5 else -v for v in vars_chosen]\n        clauses.append(clause)\n    return clauses\n\ndef run_solver(n_vars, clauses):\n    \"\"\"Lance le solveur et retourne (temps, nœuds, min_false).\"\"\"\n    solver = MaxSATSolver(clauses, n_vars)\n    t0 = time.time()\n    min_false, _ = solver.solve()\n    elapsed = time.time() - t0\n    return elapsed, solver.nodes_visited, min_false","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-04T10:49:58.344653Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-04T10:49:58.34509Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-04T10:49:58.352328Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-04T10:49:58.345055Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-04T10:49:58.35119Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":5},{"id":"8a5ba59b-f2fd-43c1-b24e-61b866464473","cell_type":"markdown","source":"### 5.1 Impact du ratio `c = m/n` (transition de phase)","metadata":{}},{"id":"27b08384-d997-4b71-87cb-3ad0394693b3","cell_type":"code","source":"N_VARS = 15\nN_REPEAT = 10\nratios = [1.0, 1.5, 2.0, 2.5, 3.0, 3.5, 4.0, 4.5, 5.0]\n\navg_nodes = []\navg_time  = []\navg_false = []\n\nfor c in ratios:\n    n_clauses = int(c * N_VARS)\n    nodes_list, time_list, false_list = [], [], []\n    for seed in range(N_REPEAT):\n        clauses = random_ksat(N_VARS, n_clauses, k=3, seed=seed)\n        t, nodes, mf = run_solver(N_VARS, clauses)\n        nodes_list.append(nodes)\n        time_list.append(t)\n        false_list.append(mf)\n    avg_nodes.append(np.mean(nodes_list))\n    avg_time.append(np.mean(time_list))\n    avg_false.append(np.mean(false_list))\n\nfig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(15, 4))\nfig.suptitle(f\"Impact du ratio c = m/n  (n={N_VARS} variables, moyenne sur {N_REPEAT} instances)\",\n             fontsize=13)\n\naxes[0].plot(ratios, avg_nodes, 'o-', color='steelblue')\naxes[0].set_xlabel('c = m/n'); axes[0].set_ylabel('Nœuds explorés')\naxes[0].set_title('Taille de l\\'arbre de recherche')\naxes[0].grid(True, alpha=0.4)\n\naxes[1].plot(ratios, avg_time, 's-', color='darkorange')\naxes[1].set_xlabel('c = m/n'); axes[1].set_ylabel('Temps (s)')\naxes[1].set_title('Temps d\\'exécution')\naxes[1].grid(True, alpha=0.4)\n\naxes[2].plot(ratios, avg_false, '^-', color='green')\naxes[2].set_xlabel('c = m/n'); axes[2].set_ylabel('Clauses fausses')\naxes[2].set_title('Qualité de la solution')\naxes[2].grid(True, alpha=0.4)\n\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.savefig('/kaggle/working/ratio_analysis.png', dpi=120, bbox_inches='tight')\nplt.show()\nprint(\"Figure sauvegardée.\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-04T10:50:03.287152Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-04T10:50:03.287556Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-04T10:50:04.529855Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-04T10:50:03.287523Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-04T10:50:04.528593Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1500x400 with 3 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}},{"name":"stdout","text":"Figure sauvegardée.\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":6},{"id":"1a9fc466-264b-414b-83ed-8c3c2aa1da0c","cell_type":"markdown","source":"### 5.2 Scalabilité en fonction de n","metadata":{}},{"id":"19e02cfc-2003-4a24-b679-48dc3c001bd5","cell_type":"code","source":"# On fixe c = 3 (zone difficile pour 3-SAT) et on fait varier n\nVAR_SIZES = [5, 8, 10, 12, 14, 16, 18]\nC_RATIO = 3.0\nN_REPEAT = 30  # au lieu de 5\n\nscale_nodes = []\nscale_time  = []\n\nfor n in VAR_SIZES:\n    n_clauses = int(C_RATIO * n)\n    nodes_list, time_list = [], []\n    for seed in range(N_REPEAT):\n        clauses = random_ksat(n, n_clauses, k=3, seed=seed)\n        t, nodes, _ = run_solver(n, clauses)\n        nodes_list.append(nodes)\n        time_list.append(t)\n    scale_nodes.append(np.mean(nodes_list))\n    scale_time.append(np.mean(time_list))\n\nfig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 4))\nfig.suptitle(f\"Scalabilité en fonction de n  (c={C_RATIO}, moyenne sur {N_REPEAT} instances)\",\n             fontsize=13)\n\n# Échelle log pour visualiser la croissance exponentielle\naxes[0].semilogy(VAR_SIZES, scale_nodes, 'o-', color='steelblue', label='Observé')\n# Référence théorique 2^n\nref = [2**n for n in VAR_SIZES]\naxes[0].semilogy(VAR_SIZES, ref, '--', color='gray', alpha=0.6, label='$2^n$ (référence)')\naxes[0].set_xlabel('n (variables)'); axes[0].set_ylabel('Nœuds explorés (log)')\naxes[0].set_title('Taille de l\\'arbre de recherche (log)')\naxes[0].legend(); axes[0].grid(True, alpha=0.4)\n\naxes[1].semilogy(VAR_SIZES, scale_time, 's-', color='darkorange')\naxes[1].set_xlabel('n (variables)'); axes[1].set_ylabel('Temps (s, log)')\naxes[1].set_title('Temps d\\'exécution (log)')\naxes[1].grid(True, alpha=0.4)\n\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.savefig('/kaggle/working/scalability_analysis.png', dpi=120, bbox_inches='tight')\nplt.show()\nprint(\"Figure sauvegardée.\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-04T10:50:16.995041Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-04T10:50:16.995358Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-04T10:50:18.716425Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-04T10:50:16.995332Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-04T10:50:18.714973Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1200x400 with 2 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}},{"name":"stdout","text":"Figure sauvegardée.\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":7},{"id":"33036af1-28e4-41b8-ac86-809120b314aa","cell_type":"markdown","source":"### 5.3 Impact de l'élagage (avec vs sans bound)","metadata":{}},{"id":"779468c5-6b88-4aa1-ab98-c4b8ffa2e829","cell_type":"code","source":"class MaxSATSolverNoBound(MaxSATSolver):\n    \"\"\"Version sans élagage : explore tout l'arbre (brute-force).\"\"\"\n\n    def _bb(self, clauses, k, assignment, assigned_vars):\n        self.nodes_visited += 1\n\n        if len(assigned_vars) == self.n:\n            total_false = k + len(clauses)\n            if total_false < self.min_false:\n                self.min_false = total_false\n                self.best_assignment = dict(assignment)\n            return\n\n        var = self._get_unassigned_var(clauses, assigned_vars)\n        if var is None:\n            total_false = k + len(clauses)\n            if total_false < self.min_false:\n                self.min_false = total_false\n            return\n\n        assigned_vars = assigned_vars | {var}\n\n        # Branche True — sans élagage\n        new_clauses, added_false = self._apply_literal(clauses, var)\n        assignment[var] = True\n        self._bb(new_clauses, k + added_false, assignment, assigned_vars)\n\n        # Branche False — sans élagage\n        new_clauses, added_false = self._apply_literal(clauses, -var)\n        assignment[var] = False\n        self._bb(new_clauses, k + added_false, assignment, assigned_vars)\n\n        if var in assignment:\n            del assignment[var]\n\n\n# Comparaison sur différentes tailles\nN_REPEAT = 10\nsizes = [6, 8, 10, 12, 14]\n\nnodes_bb, nodes_bf = [], []\n\nfor n in sizes:\n    n_clauses = int(3 * n)\n    bb_list, bf_list = [], []\n    for seed in range(N_REPEAT):\n        clauses = random_ksat(n, n_clauses, k=3, seed=seed)\n\n        s_bb = MaxSATSolver(clauses, n)\n        s_bb.solve()\n        bb_list.append(s_bb.nodes_visited)\n\n        s_bf = MaxSATSolverNoBound(clauses, n)\n        s_bf.solve()\n        bf_list.append(s_bf.nodes_visited)\n\n    nodes_bb.append(np.mean(bb_list))\n    nodes_bf.append(np.mean(bf_list))\n\nfig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 5))\nax.semilogy(sizes, nodes_bf, 'o--', color='red',      label='Sans élagage (brute-force)')\nax.semilogy(sizes, nodes_bb, 's-',  color='steelblue', label='Branch & Bound (avec élagage)')\nax.set_xlabel('n (variables)')\nax.set_ylabel('Nœuds explorés (log)')\nax.set_title('Efficacité de l\\'élagage Branch & Bound vs Brute-Force')\nax.legend()\nax.grid(True, alpha=0.4)\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.savefig('/kaggle/working/pruning_comparison.png', dpi=120, bbox_inches='tight')\nplt.show()\nprint(\"Figure sauvegardée.\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-04T10:50:50.030707Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-04T10:50:50.031103Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-04T10:50:51.459736Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-04T10:50:50.031071Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-04T10:50:51.458285Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 800x500 with 1 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}},{"name":"stdout","text":"Figure sauvegardée.\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":8},{"id":"70c37132-6ea4-49d8-8796-0a86473c8ae5","cell_type":"markdown","source":"### 5.4 Tableau récapitulatif","metadata":{}},{"id":"5c4ae2dc-c7aa-44a7-9714-39b7b0d18d65","cell_type":"code","sourc